rComments: PSY4727 is not what I was expected - you learn very little about dreams. Most of this class is about the physiological processes of sleep. Nevertheless, Robillard makes the class easy. Lectures are clear and exams are extremely fair. There is one lab assignment, but it is very straightforward. There are no required readings.

She's a really nice prof but her class is long and boring for no reason. She can do the class in max 2h but most of the time she takes 3h. We have a quiz every week but they're easy. midterm was 3h long which is super long for a midterm. Sweet and caring prof but needs to do something about how boring her class is
Caring professor, knows a lot on the matter and it shows. Exams are not tricky, professor Robillard is fair and gives good feedback
